Based on my comprehensive research, I can now provide you with a detailed report on implementing right-click context menu functionality in Adobe Premiere Pro.

---

# Premiere Pro Right-Click Context Menu Research Report

**Documented for:** Premiere Pro 25.6+ (November 2025)
**Platform Status:** CEP supported until ~September 2026; UXP is the new standard

---

## Executive Summary

**The bad news:** You **cannot** add items to Premiere Pro's native right-click context menu (the one that appears when right-clicking on the timeline). This is a hard limitation of the platform.

**The good news:** There are several viable alternative approaches that can achieve similar workflows, and I have detailed implementation guidance for each.

---

## 1. CEP/ExtendScript Context Menu Support

### Can CEP plugins add items to Premiere's native right-click context menu?

**No.** This is explicitly confirmed in Adobe community discussions:

> "Script-based commands cannot be added to context menus in Premiere Pro. PPro's context menus are not externally customizable."
> -- [Adobe Community Discussion](https://community.adobe.com/t5/premiere-pro-discussions/can-i-customize-the-right-click-menu/td-p/12346592)

### What Context Menu APIs ARE Available?

CEP panels support two types of menus:

#### A. Panel Flyout Menu (hamburger menu in panel header)
```javascript
// XML menu definition
var flyoutXML = '<Menu>' +
    '<MenuItem Id="spliceVoice" Label="SPLICE: Process with Voice Isolation" Enabled="true" Checked="false"/>' +
    '<MenuItem Id="spliceNoVoice" Label="SPLICE: Process without Voice Isolation" Enabled="true" Checked="false"/>' +
    '<MenuItem Label="---" />' +
    '<MenuItem Id="settings" Label="Settings..." Enabled="true" Checked="false"/>' +
'</Menu>';

// Set the flyout menu
csInterface.setPanelFlyoutMenu(flyoutXML);

// Listen for menu clicks
csInterface.addEventListener("com.adobe.csxs.events.flyoutMenuClicked", function(event) {
    var menuId = event.data.menuId;
    if (menuId === "spliceVoice") {
        processSelectedClips(true); // with voice isolation
    } else if (menuId === "spliceNoVoice") {
        processSelectedClips(false); // without voice isolation
    }
});
```

#### B. Context Menu WITHIN Your Panel (right-click inside your panel's HTML)
```javascript
// Context menu within your CEP panel
var contextMenuXML = '<Menu>' +
    '<MenuItem Id="spliceVoice" Label="SPLICE: Process with Voice Isolation" Enabled="true" Icon="./icons/voice.png"/>' +
    '<MenuItem Id="spliceNoVoice" Label="SPLICE: Process without Voice Isolation" Enabled="true" Icon="./icons/no-voice.png"/>' +
'</Menu>';

csInterface.setContextMenu(contextMenuXML, function(menuId) {
    if (menuId === "spliceVoice") {
        processSelectedClips(true);
    } else if (menuId === "spliceNoVoice") {
        processSelectedClips(false);
    }
});

csInterface.addEventListener("com.adobe.csxs.events.contextMenuClicked", menuClickHandler);
```

**Limitation:** This context menu only appears when right-clicking inside your panel's HTML area, not on the timeline.

Sources:
- [CEP 11.1 HTML Extension Cookbook](https://github.com/Adobe-CEP/CEP-Resources/blob/master/CEP_11.x/Documentation/CEP%2011.1%20HTML%20Extension%20Cookbook.md)
- [HTML Panels Tips: #14 Flyout Menu](https://www.davidebarranca.com/2014/10/html-panels-tips-14-flyout-menu/)

---

## 2. UXP Context Menu Support

### Does UXP for Premiere support context menus on the timeline?

**No.** UXP (Unified eXtensibility Platform) in Premiere Pro also does not provide access to native timeline context menus. UXP provides:

1. **Command entrypoints** - Menu items under `Window > UXP Plugins > [Your Plugin]`
2. **Panel entrypoints** - Dockable panels with custom UI

### UXP Command Implementation

```json
// manifest.json
{
  "manifestVersion": 5,
  "id": "com.yourcompany.splice",
  "name": "SPLICE Audio Processing",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "main": "index.js",
  "host": {
    "app": "PremierePro",
    "minVersion": "25.6"
  },
  "entrypoints": [
    {
      "type": "command",
      "id": "processWithVoiceIsolation",
      "label": "SPLICE: Process with Voice Isolation"
    },
    {
      "type": "command", 
      "id": "processWithoutVoiceIsolation",
      "label": "SPLICE: Process without Voice Isolation"
    },
    {
      "type": "panel",
      "id": "splicePanel",
      "label": "SPLICE Panel"
    }
  ]
}
```

```javascript
// index.js
const { entrypoints } = require("uxp");

entrypoints.setup({
  commands: {
    processWithVoiceIsolation: async () => {
      await processSelectedClips(true);
    },
    processWithoutVoiceIsolation: async () => {
      await processSelectedClips(false);
    }
  }
});
```

**Location:** These commands appear under `Window > UXP Plugins > SPLICE Audio Processing`

**Note:** Keyboard shortcuts are not yet available in UXP for Premiere Pro.

Sources:
- [Adding command entrypoints to your plugin](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/plugins/tutorials/adding-command-entrypoints/)
- [UXP Manifest](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/plugins/concepts/manifest/)
- [Panels and Commands](https://developer.adobe.com/premiere-pro/uxp/plugins/concepts/panels-and-commands/)

---

## 3. Alternative Approaches (Recommended)

### Option A: Panel with Selection Detection (BEST APPROACH)

Create a dockable panel that shows selected clips and provides action buttons.

```javascript
// ExtendScript (Premiere.jsx)
$._PPP_ = {
    getSelectedClipsInfo: function() {
        var selection = app.project.activeSequence.getSelection();
        var clipInfo = [];

        for (var i = 0; i < selection.length; i++) {
            var clip = selection[i];
            clipInfo.push({
                name: clip.name,
                start: clip.start.seconds,
                end: clip.end.seconds,
                duration: clip.duration.seconds,
                trackIndex: clip.parentTrackIndex,
                mediaType: clip.mediaType
            });
        }
        return JSON.stringify(clipInfo);
    },

    processClipsWithVoiceIsolation: function(voiceIsolation) {
        var selection = app.project.activeSequence.getSelection();
        if (selection.length === 0) {
            return JSON.stringify({error: "No clips selected"});
        }

        // Your processing logic here
        var result = {
            clipCount: selection.length,
            voiceIsolation: voiceIsolation,
            status: "processing"
        };

        return JSON.stringify(result);
    }
};

// Register for selection change events
app.bind("onActiveSequenceSelectionChanged", function() {
    // Send event to CEP panel via Vulcan messaging
    var eventObj = new CSXSEvent();
    eventObj.type = "com.splice.selectionChanged";
    eventObj.data = $._PPP_.getSelectedClipsInfo();
    eventObj.dispatch();
});
```

```html
<!-- Panel HTML (index.html) -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>SPLICE Audio Processing</title>
    <script src="js/CSInterface.js"></script>
    <style>
        body { 
            font-family: Adobe Clean, sans-serif; 
            background: #232323; 
            color: #e0e0e0;
            padding: 15px;
        }
        .selection-info {
            background: #1a1a1a;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .btn {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 12px;
            margin: 5px 0;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 14px;
        }
        .btn-voice { background: #0078d4; color: white; }
        .btn-no-voice { background: #4a4a4a; color: white; }
        .btn:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed; }
        .progress { display: none; margin-top: 15px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="selection-info">
        <strong>Selected Clips:</strong>
        <div id="clipCount">0 clips selected</div>
        <div id="clipList"></div>
    </div>

    <button class="btn btn-voice" id="btnVoice" disabled>
        SPLICE: Process with Voice Isolation
    </button>

    <button class="btn btn-no-voice" id="btnNoVoice" disabled>
        SPLICE: Process without Voice Isolation
    </button>

    <div class="progress" id="progress">
        <div>Processing...</div>
        <progress id="progressBar" max="100" value="0"></progress>
    </div>

    <script src="js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

```javascript
// Panel JavaScript (main.js)
var csInterface = new CSInterface();

// Listen for selection changes
csInterface.addEventListener("com.splice.selectionChanged", function(event) {
    updateSelectionUI(JSON.parse(event.data));
});

// Initial selection check
refreshSelection();

function refreshSelection() {
    csInterface.evalScript("$._PPP_.getSelectedClipsInfo()", function(result) {
        if (result !== "undefined") {
            updateSelectionUI(JSON.parse(result));
        }
    });
}

function updateSelectionUI(clips) {
    var count = clips.length;
    document.getElementById("clipCount").textContent = count + " clip(s) selected";

    var listHtml = clips.map(function(c) {
        return "<div>" + c.name + " (" + c.duration.toFixed(2) + "s)</div>";
    }).join("");
    document.getElementById("clipList").innerHTML = listHtml;

    // Enable/disable buttons based on selection
    var hasSelection = count > 0;
    document.getElementById("btnVoice").disabled = !hasSelection;
    document.getElementById("btnNoVoice").disabled = !hasSelection;
}

document.getElementById("btnVoice").addEventListener("click", function() {
    processClips(true);
});

document.getElementById("btnNoVoice").addEventListener("click", function() {
    processClips(false);
});

function processClips(withVoiceIsolation) {
    document.getElementById("progress").style.display = "block";

    csInterface.evalScript(
        "$._PPP_.processClipsWithVoiceIsolation(" + withVoiceIsolation + ")",
        function(result) {
            var response = JSON.parse(result);
            if (response.error) {
                alert(response.error);
            } else {
                // Trigger your processing pipeline
                startProcessingPipeline(response.clipCount, withVoiceIsolation);
            }
        }
    );
}

function startProcessingPipeline(clipCount, withVoiceIsolation) {
    // Your Node.js / external processing integration here
    // Use csInterface.evalScript to communicate back and forth
}
```

### Option B: Keyboard Shortcuts

Use the ExtendScript Hotkey Manager plugin or create a CEP panel with keypress listeners:

```javascript
// In your CEP panel JavaScript
document.addEventListener("keydown", function(e) {
    // Only respond when panel is focused
    if (e.ctrlKey && e.shiftKey && e.key === "V") {
        e.preventDefault();
        processClips(true); // Voice isolation
    }
    if (e.ctrlKey && e.shiftKey && e.key === "N") {
        e.preventDefault();
        processClips(false); // No voice isolation
    }
});
```

**Limitation:** Keyboard shortcuts only work when your panel has focus.

Sources:
- [How To: Assign Keyboard Shortcuts to ExtendScript](https://vakago-tools.com/assign-hotkeys-to-extendscript-in-adobe-applications/)

### Option C: Menu Bar Integration via UXP Commands

As shown in Section 2, UXP commands appear under `Window > UXP Plugins`. This is the closest to native menu integration available.

---

## 4. Implementation Methods - Selection APIs

### ExtendScript Selection API

```javascript
// Get selected clips
var selection = app.project.activeSequence.getSelection();

// Returns TrackItemCollection (array-like)
// Each item is a TrackItem object with properties:
// - name: string
// - start: Time object
// - end: Time object  
// - duration: Time object
// - inPoint: Time object
// - outPoint: Time object
// - mediaType: string ("Video", "Audio")
// - parentTrackIndex: number
// - components: ComponentCollection (effects)
// - projectItem: ProjectItem (source media)

// Check if items are selected
if (selection.length > 0) {
    for (var i = 0; i < selection.length; i++) {
        var clip = selection[i];
        // Process each clip
    }
}
```

### Selection Change Event

```javascript
// Register for selection change events
app.bind("onActiveSequenceSelectionChanged", function() {
    var selection = app.project.activeSequence.getSelection();
    // Handle the new selection
});

// Other useful events
app.bind("onActiveSequenceChanged", function() {
    // Different sequence became active
});

app.bind("onActiveSequenceStructureChanged", function() {
    // Clips were added/removed/moved
});
```

Sources:
- [Sequence object - Premiere Pro Scripting Guide](https://ppro-scripting.docsforadobe.dev/sequence/sequence/)
- [Adobe Community - Selected clip in timeline?](https://community.adobe.com/t5/premiere-pro-discussions/selected-clip-in-timeline/td-p/8233928)

---

## 5. QE (Undocumented) API

The QE API is an undocumented API that provides additional functionality. To check if it has context menu capabilities:

```javascript
// Enable QE API
app.enableQE();

// Explore available methods
var methods = qe.reflect.methods;

// Known useful QE methods:
// qe.project.getActiveSequence()
// qe.project.undo()
// qe.project.getVideoEffectList()
// QETrackItem.addVideoEffect()
// qe.project.getActiveSequence().exportFramePNG()
```

**Important:** The QE API is undocumented and unsupported. Objects from the standard DOM (like `getSelection()` results) are incompatible with QE DOM objects.

Sources:
- [Understanding the Adobe Premiere Pro QE API](https://vakago-tools.com/premiere-pro-qe-api/)
- [Unofficial Premiere Pro CC API](https://vidjuheffex.github.io/ppro.api/)

---

## 6. Recommended Workflow Design

### Architecture

```
[User selects clips on timeline]
         |
         v
[Selection change event fires]
         |
         v
[CEP Panel updates to show selected clips]
         |
         v
[User clicks button in panel OR uses keyboard shortcut]
         |
         v
[ExtendScript collects clip metadata]
         |
         v
[Node.js in CEP handles processing]
         |
         v
[Progress shown in panel]
         |
         v
[Results applied back to timeline]
```

### Complete Processing Pipeline

```javascript
// ExtendScript layer (Premiere.jsx)
$._PPP_ = {
    exportForProcessing: function(voiceIsolation) {
        var selection = app.project.activeSequence.getSelection();
        var exportData = [];

        for (var i = 0; i < selection.length; i++) {
            var clip = selection[i];
            var projectItem = clip.projectItem;

            exportData.push({
                clipIndex: i,
                name: clip.name,
                sourcePath: projectItem.getMediaPath(),
                inPoint: clip.inPoint.seconds,
                outPoint: clip.outPoint.seconds,
                voiceIsolation: voiceIsolation
            });
        }

        return JSON.stringify(exportData);
    },

    replaceClipMedia: function(clipIndex, newMediaPath) {
        var selection = app.project.activeSequence.getSelection();
        if (clipIndex < selection.length) {
            var clip = selection[clipIndex];
            // Import new media and replace
            var importedItem = app.project.importFiles([newMediaPath]);
            // Additional replacement logic here
        }
    }
};
```

```javascript
// Node.js layer in CEP panel (main.js)
var path = require('path');
var childProcess = require('child_process');

function processClips(withVoiceIsolation) {
    csInterface.evalScript(
        "$._PPP_.exportForProcessing(" + withVoiceIsolation + ")",
        function(result) {
            var clips = JSON.parse(result);
            processClipsSequentially(clips, 0);
        }
    );
}

function processClipsSequentially(clips, index) {
    if (index >= clips.length) {
        alert("Processing complete!");
        return;
    }

    var clip = clips[index];
    updateProgress(index, clips.length);

    // Call your external processing tool
    var args = [
        clip.sourcePath,
        "--in", clip.inPoint,
        "--out", clip.outPoint,
        "--voice-isolation", clip.voiceIsolation
    ];

    var process = childProcess.spawn('/path/to/your/processor', args);

    process.on('close', function(code) {
        if (code === 0) {
            // Processing succeeded, continue to next clip
            processClipsSequentially(clips, index + 1);
        } else {
            alert("Error processing: " + clip.name);
        }
    });
}
```

---

## 7. Summary and Recommendations

| Approach | Native Feel | Implementation Effort | Stability |
|----------|-------------|----------------------|-----------|
| Panel with Buttons | Medium | Low | High |
| Panel Flyout Menu | High | Low | High |
| UXP Commands | High | Medium | Medium |
| Keyboard Shortcuts | Low | Low | Medium |

### Best Practice Recommendation

1. **Primary Interface:** Create a CEP panel with prominent buttons for your two processing options
2. **Secondary Interface:** Add a panel flyout menu with the same options
3. **Selection Feedback:** Display selected clip count and names in the panel
4. **Progress Indicator:** Show processing progress in the panel
5. **Future-Proofing:** Plan for UXP migration as CEP support ends ~September 2026

